definition: early part (of a decade, century etc)/the first years

sentences.english: Napoleon stood astride the early 19th century like a giant.
sentences.chinese: 拿破崙像個巨人跨越19世紀初葉。

sentences.english: It seems that Freemasonry developed in Europe in the early eighteenth century.
sentences.chinese: 共濟會似乎在十八世紀初葉在歐洲開始發展。
